<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 5:13PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Millard and north central Beaver Counties through 600 PM MDT...
At 513 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Milford, moving northeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Millard and north central Beaver Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
